<heading id="1A46603D4202895AFF755A92FE91C1BB" bold="true" box="[227,341,477,503]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="5" pageNumber="15" reason="3">
<emphasis id="73C50B434202895AFF755A92FE91C1BB" bold="true" box="[227,341,477,503]" pageId="5" pageNumber="15">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="410ED7514202895AFF755943FCDDC2FA" blockId="5.[225,1436,524,694]" pageId="5" pageNumber="15">
<taxonomicName id="86B1ACD24202895AFF755943FE17C26A" authorityName="Bensaid" authorityYear="1974" box="[227,467,524,550]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Ponticeratidae" genus="Pseudoprobeloceras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ammonoidea" pageId="5" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="73C50B434202895AFF755943FE17C26A" box="[227,467,524,550]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="15">Pseudoprobeloceras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be considered the stratigraphically earliest and morphologically simplest genus of the gephuroceratids. The most important morphological feature is the very low median saddle, which is indicative of a newly acquired trait. In the early forms of 
<taxonomicName id="86B1ACD24202895AFC0F591BFBDCC221" authorityName="Matern" authorityYear="1929" box="[921,1048,596,621]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Ponticeratidae" genus="Ponticeras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ammonoidea" pageId="5" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="73C50B434202895AFC0F591BFBDCC221" box="[921,1048,596,621]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="15">Ponticeras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which have the same suture line formula as 
<taxonomicName id="86B1ACD24202895AFEFB5938FD9FC2DD" authorityName="Bensaid" authorityYear="1974" box="[365,603,631,657]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Ponticeratidae" genus="Pseudoprobeloceras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ammonoidea" pageId="5" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="73C50B434202895AFEFB5938FD9FC2DD" box="[365,603,631,657]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="15">Pseudoprobeloceras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the median saddle is already much more prominent and the external lobe is much wider than in 
<taxonomicName id="86B1ACD24202895AFDB459D4FCD6C2F9" authorityName="Bensaid" authorityYear="1974" box="[546,786,667,693]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Ponticeratidae" genus="Pseudoprobeloceras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ammonoidea" pageId="5" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="73C50B434202895AFDB459D4FCD6C2F9" box="[546,786,667,693]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="15">Pseudoprobeloceras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
